This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing and specifically on abstractive summarization, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also heavily relies on neural network models, which are a common tool in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses transfer learning, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of summarization performance using ROUGE scores, which is a common metric in information retrieval (cs.IR).
